English: UPLINK VERIFICATION CODES SENT TO {0} AS LOG FILES.
Description: A text that appears on screen to inform the player that verification codes (passwords) have been transferred via a computer network to a specific computer terminal and saved on that terminal as a log file. "{0}" will be replaced by the name of the computer terminal; do not alter those characters, just make sure they are in the gramatically correct position in the sentence.
